radiographic_examinations.findings: New bilateral diffuse, scattered, and occasionally clustered microcalcifications in regional distributions in both breasts, predominantly in the left lower inner quadrant; no associated masses, breast edema, architectural distortion, or lymphadenopathy.

Patchy heterogeneous abnormal enhancement throughout both breasts, most prominent in the lower inner and upper outer quadrants of the left breast; slow initial enhancement and continued progressive enhancement over time.
Numerous bilateral simple fluid-filled cavities, representing cysts and dilated ducts, without discrete solid masses.
